      "countAsQuest:1": 1,
      "desc:8": "§2Fluorophlogopite§2§r is the industrial answer to Mica-based foils, and something you\u0027ll want to start investing in as higher tier coils cost increasingly more foil to make.\n\nThe recipe for making Raw Fluorophlogopite Dust is done in the MV mixer. While all of the new dusts involved may look a little daunting, they\u0027re not that bad. You will need the following:\n\n- Some variant of quartz dust: Any one of Quartz Sand, Quartzite, Nether Quartz, or Certus Quartz\n- Alumina\n- Potassiumfluorosilicate, which is made in two steps by combining Rock Salt, Hydrofluoric Acid, and Raw Silicon\n- Potassium Carbonate, made by combining Potassium Dust and Oxygen (or Potash to cover both) with Carbon Dioxide in a Chemical Reactor\n\nThe exact ratios of each ingredient depend on the form of quartz that you\u0027re using, as does the exact amount of raw dust that you get from the recipe.\n\n[note]Technically, this process is entirely optional, but highly recommended. The raw dust is also used in ZPM, but Mica can be substituted for that use case if you would like.[/note]",
